  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 24 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 3 critical, 17 high, 6 medium, 13 normal. Key bases needing attention include Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR), Katowice Wojciech Korfanty (KTW/EPKT) and Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP); plus 17 other bases. 6 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is snow-related runway contamination risk, mist and fog / freezing fog  — most notably around Modlin (WMI/EPMO), Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD) and Vilnius (VNO/EYVI). Network hotspots: Modlin (WMI/EPMO), Josep Tarradellas Barcelona-El Prat (BCN/LEBL), Lamezia Terme Sant'Eufemia (SUF/LICA), Malta (MLA/LMML), Berlin Brandenburg Willy Brandt (BER/EDDB) and 19 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, snow / blowing snow and RVR limitations. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Josep Tarradellas Barcelona-El Prat (BCN/LEBL), Lamezia Terme Sant'Eufemia (SUF/LICA), Malta (MLA/LMML) and 9 others.",
